{
  "message": "fuzz(repair-symbols): 22 structured seeds across all three parsers and error paths\n\nfuzz_repair_symbols drives RepairBlockHeader::parse,\nRepairGroupDescExt::parse, and SymbolDigest::parse on the same input\nand asserts (a) parse determinism and (b) round-trip equivalence\nthrough to_bytes / parse. Existing 6 ad-hoc seeds covered only one\nvalid example per parser; the CRC-mismatch / bad-magic / truncated\nerror branches and the boundary-value cases were never exercised at\nseed time.\n\nAdds 22 seeds covering:\n\n  RepairBlockHeader (32 bytes):\n  * default (esi=0, count=1, size=64, group=0, gen=0)\n  * realistic (esi=0x100, count=64, size=4096, group=42, gen=0x5A)\n  * max-value (every field at its u32/u16/u64 maximum)\n  * symbol_count=0 (degenerate but legal: payload_size=0)\n  * symbol_size=0 (degenerate)\n  * corrupt CRC (byte at offset 24 XOR'd with 0xFF)\n  * truncated to 28 bytes (missing reserved tail)\n  * bad magic (0xDEADBEEF instead of REPAIR_BLOCK_MAGIC)\n\n  RepairGroupDescExt (48 bytes):\n  * default\n  * realistic 128 MiB group (transfer_length=128M, symbol_size=4096,\n    source_block_count=8192, repair_block_count=64)\n  * max u64::MAX repair_generation\n  * truncated to 44 bytes\n  * corrupt CRC\n  * bad magic\n  * all-zero payload with a valid CRC over those zeros\n\n  SymbolDigest (36 bytes):\n  * default\n  * realistic (esi=0xCAFEBABE, digest=0..31)\n  * max esi\n  * truncated to 35 bytes\n  * zero esi with non-zero digest\n\n  Cross-parser:\n  * concatenated valid header + group_desc + digest in one input\n  * 4-byte universal seed (drives every parser's InsufficientData\n    branch in one run)\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 3.6 M executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
